1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"https://orbtr.net/?p=3786\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:757:\"<p>It&#8217;s not a secret: online marketing is huge right now and it isn&#8217;t going anywhere. Forrester predicts that by the end of 2016, spending on interactive marketing will clear $76 BILLION, representing a more than 120% increase since 2011. Obviously sales/marketing software — like the software ORBTR makes — factors into that number and represents about [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://orbtr.net/blog/the-economics-of-online-marketing-and-what-most-firms-and-practitioners-dont-tell-you/\">The economics of online marketing and what most firms and practitioners DON&#8217;T tell you&#8230;</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://orbtr.net\">ORBTR.NET - Sales &amp; Marketing Wordpress Plugin</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"admin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8313:\"<p>It&#8217;s not a secret: online marketing is huge right now and it isn&#8217;t going anywhere. Forrester predicts that by the end of 2016, spending on interactive marketing will clear $76 BILLION, representing a more than 120% increase since 2011.</p>\n<p>Obviously sales/marketing software — like the software ORBTR makes — factors into that number and represents about 7% of that online spend.</p>\n<h3>Only 7%?!! I thought automated sales and marketing was the next big thing!</h3>\n<p>No, 7% doesn&#8217;t sound like a lot, but it makes perfect sense because online success requires much more than software. The software is a tool, not a strategy, not content, not advertising media, not the people or agencies that you need to implement the strategies. So really, 7% sounds about right.</p>\n<h3>Here&#8217;s where the math gets funky&#8230;</h3>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-3787 size-full\" src=\"https://orbtr.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/math.jpg\" alt=\"math-online-marketing\" width=\"960\" height=\"673\" srcset=\"https://orbtr.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/math.jpg 960w, https://orbtr.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/math-300x210.jpg 300w, https://orbtr.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/math-630x442.jpg 630w, https://orbtr.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/math-305x214.jpg 305w, https://orbtr.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/math-630x442-360x252.jpg 360w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\" /></p>\n<p>Let&#8217;s take that 7% and use it as a guidepost to figure out what your total marketing budget should be based the cost of the software that you&#8217;re hearing so much about. Based on that ratio, users of the popular Hubspot automation software would have to have a digital marketing budget of about $180,000. Users of Infusionsoft? $86,000. Marketo? Over $200,000.</p>\n<p><strong>There are millions of small companies in the US alone —in fact more than 99% of all US-based business are small and midsize businesses — and most of them don&#8217;t have marketing budgets (much less digital and online marketing budgets) anywhere near the necessary levels to justify the expense of one of the major software packages.</strong></p>\n<h3>But that doesn&#8217;t mean that small businesses can&#8217;t afford sales and marketing software</h3>\n<p>This is exactly why ORBTR is here. Our flagship product <a href=\"https://orbtr.net/features/\">ORBTR Connect</a> can be bought for just $990/year and <a href=\"https://orbtr.net/torq\">ORBTR Torq</a> for just $249/year, which means they can earn their keep within relatively small annual marketing budgets of just $14,000 and $3500 respectively.</p>\n<p><strong>We built our software to be the only true option for small organizations looking to build better, more automated sales and online marketing processes on a budget. </strong></p>\n<h3>Let us prove it:</h3>\n<p>Enter your information below and you&#8217;ll be started on an automated campaign that I put together this morning. It uses Gravity Forms (though many other form handlers could work as well), ORBTR Torq (just $249/year), a free <a href=\"http://zapier.com\" target=\"_blank\">Zapier</a> account, and a paid MailChimp account ($10/month and up depending on the size of your mailing list, needed for autoresponders).</p>\n<p><strong>Give marketing automation a spin by filling out the form below&#8230;</strong></p>\n\n                <div class=\'gf_browser_unknown gform_wrapper\' id=\'gform_wrapper_101\' ><form method=\'post\' enctype=\'multipart/form-data\'  id=\'gform_101\'  action=\'/feed/\'>\n                        <div class=\'gform_body\'><ul id=\'gform_fields_101\' class=\'gform_fields top_label form_sublabel_below description_below\'><li id=\'field_101_1\' class=\'gfield gfield_contains_required field_sublabel_below field_description_below\' ><label class=\'gfield_label\' for=\'input_101_1_3\' >Name<span class=\'gfield_required\'>*</span></label><div class=\'ginput_complex ginput_container no_prefix has_first_name no_middle_name has_last_name no_suffix\' id=\'input_101_1\'>\n                            <span id=\'input_101_1_3_container\' class=\'name_first\' >\n                                                    <input type=\'text\' name=\'input_1.3\' id=\'input_101_1_3\' value=\'\' aria-label=\'First name\' tabindex=\'1\'  />\n                                                    <label for=\'input_101_1_3\' >First</label>\n                                               </span>\n                            <span id=\'input_101_1_6_container\' class=\'nam