15 13:00:16 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"News\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"https://orbtr.net/?p=3771\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:871:\"<p>&#8211; Partly funded by MailChimp, Torq offers a service that grabs the attention of potential clients with individually crafted emails, also offering email marketing metrics and integrated lead tracking in one manageable interface. &#8211; Torq opens doors and increases sales for companies and services of all shapes and sizes, bypassing other costly solutions that are [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://orbtr.net/blog/orbtr-announces-release-of-torq-aims-to-maximize-results-by-adding-personal-touch-to-sales-emails-and-bringing-online-tracking-to-offline-leads/\">ORBTR Announces Release Of Torq, Aims To Maximize Results By Adding Personal Touch To Sales Emails And Bringing Online Tracking to “Offline” Leads</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://orbtr.net\">ORBTR.NET - Sales &amp; Marketing Wordpress Plugin</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"admin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5769:\"<p><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-3772 size-full\" src=\"https://orbtr.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/torq-cover.jpg\" alt=\"torq-cover-lead-tracking-system\" width=\"1000\" height=\"563\" srcset=\"https://orbtr.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/torq-cover.jpg 1000w, https://orbtr.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/torq-cover-300x169.jpg 300w, https://orbtr.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/torq-cover-630x355.jpg 630w, https://orbtr.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/torq-cover-305x172.jpg 305w, https://orbtr.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/torq-cover-630x355-360x202.jpg 360w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" /></p>\n<p><em>&#8211; Partly funded by MailChimp, Torq offers a service that grabs the attention of potential clients with individually crafted emails, also offering email marketing metrics and integrated lead tracking in one manageable interface.</em></p>\n<p><em>&#8211; Torq opens doors and increases sales for companies and services of all shapes and sizes, bypassing other costly solutions that are often complicated to users with no background in marketing.</em></p>\n<p><em>-“Companies will love using Torq for its simple and intuitive setup, which takes just a few minutes. It doesn’t matter what you know about lead tracking or email marketing, from the first click Torq is designed to be accessible for any user,”- Founder Erik Wolf.</em></p>\n<p><strong>March 18, 2015</strong> – Colorado-based ORBTR announces release of the <a href=\"https://orbtr.net/torq/\">Torq email and lead tracking system</a>, aims to improve effectiveness and maximize the results of sales emails.</p>\n<p>Torq is a new sales prospecting email and lead tracking system which aims to maximize sales results by providing personalized email outreach for a business’ customers. To complement this tailored outreach, the Torq platform features essential email marketing metrics and integrated lead tracking, allowing businesses to analyze messages and prospects via one centralized interface.</p>\n<p>With the marketing power that increased global connectivity has allowed, people are less willing to give the time of day to an email which looks like it has been mass sent to thousands of people. Torq allows salespeople to craft personal emails that behave like email marketing: measuring opens and clicks and tracking a lead’s behavior on the company website, and helping sales teams maximize a prospect’s attention.</p>\n<p>Additionally, Torq provides real-time alerts, telling you exactly when leads are viewing your website and what they are looking at — helping salespeople understand when their prospects are most interested, helping them shorten sales cycles and seal more deals.</p>\n<p>“Email is the basis for a majority of business communications — but most of us don’t use it very effectively, especially in sales and prospecting efforts,” says Erik Wolf, Founder of ORBTR. “How are we measuring the effectiveness of our sales emails? How are we using it to shepherd a qualified lead through the sales funnel? How are we using our follow-ups to shorten the sales cycle? With Torq this complicated world is condenses into one simple, easily accessible interface,” he adds.</p>\n<p>According to Wolf, although existing email marketing tools such as MailChimp and ConstantContact include analytics which can be used to measure the effectiveness of email marketing activity, these platforms rely entirely on mass messages. Torq compliments these traditional “one to many” email marketing messages with the ability to do “one to one” email marketing — a function which is typically handled by a personal email client and misses the ability to track and measure results.</p>\n<p>Torq includes functionality that integrates with Mandrill, a leading transactional email system by MailChimp. In addition to providing the backbone for the email portion of the product, MailChimp’s integrations team provided guidance and feedback throughout the process and financially backed a portion of the development through their Integration Fund.</p>\n<p>Torq also provides integration with Zapier, which allows the user to share lead tracking data with over 300 popular web applications, including email marketing tools, Customer Relation Management programs (CRMs), task management apps and more.</p>\n<p>“Companies will love using Torq for it’s simple and intuitive setup, which takes just a few minutes.  It doesn’t matter what you know about lead tracking or email marketing, from the first click Torq is designed to be accessible for any user,” Wolf explains.</p>\n<p>While leading competitors offer similar functions, they are often expensive and complicated to those with no background in marketing or analytics. Market email service Tout offers a useful tool-set and has a strong following, but at $3000 a year, may be out of reach for small and start-up businesses.</p>\n<p>At only $249 per year, ORBTR’s Torq aims to open to the doors of effective, user-friendly sales email and lead tracking system at a reasonable price for companies of all shapes and sizes.</p>\n<div id=\"themify_builder_content-3771\" data-postid=\"3771\" class=\"themify_builder_content themify_builder_content-3771 themify_builder themify_builder_front\">\n\n	</div>\n<!-- /themify_builder_content --><p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://orbtr.net/blog/orbtr-announces-release-of-torq-aims-to-maximize-results-by-adding-personal-touch-to-sales-emails-and-bringing-online-tracking-to-offline-leads/\">ORBTR Announces Release Of Torq, Aims To Maximize Results By Adding Personal Touch To Sales Emails And Bringing Online Tracking to “Offline” Leads</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://orbtr.net\">ORBTR.NET - Sales &amp; Marketing Wordpress Plugin</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:172:\"https://orbtr.net/blog/orbtr-announces-release-of-torq-aims-to-maximize-results-by-adding-personal-touch-to-sales-emails-and-bringing-online-tracking-to-offline-leads/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:43:\"ORBTR releases “Bot-Less” version 2.9.1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:61:\"https://orbtr.net/blog/orbtr-releases-bot-less-version-2-9-1/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:69:\"https://orbtr.net/blog/orbtr-releases-bot-less-version-2-9-1/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Fri, 06 Mar 2015 15:14:50 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"News\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"https://orbtr.net/?p=3739\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:610:\"<p>ORBTR 2.9.1 is hitting WordPress sites everywhere this morning and it includes several big changes from our last major release, version 2.9 which was unveiled in December. You will no longer see search bots in your tracking history! The robots are gone from ORBTR for good! That means that the people you see in your [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://orbtr.net/blog/orbtr-releases-bot-less-version-2-9-1/\">ORBTR releases &#8220;Bot-Less&#8221; version 2.9.1</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://orbtr.net\">ORBTR.NET - Sales &amp; Marketing Wordpress Plugin</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"admin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6497:\"<p><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-3740 size-full\" src=\"https://orbtr.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/bots.jpg\" alt=\"orbtr-gravity-forms-update\" width=\"900\" height=\"600\" srcset=\"https://orbtr.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/bots.jpg 900w, https://orbtr.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/bots-300x200.jpg 300w, https://orbtr.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/bots-630x420.jpg 630w, https://orbtr.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/bots-305x203.jpg 305w, https://orbtr.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/bots-630x420-360x240.jpg 360w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px\" /></p>\n<p>ORBTR 2.9.1 is hitting WordPress sites everywhere this morning and it includes several big changes from our last major release, version 2.9 which was unveiled in December.</p>\n<h3>You will no longer see search bots in your tracking history!</h3>\n<p>The robots are gone from ORBTR for good! That means that the people you see in your visitor and intelligence report on ORBTR are all going to be actual humans from this point forward. We will make no guarantees as to the quality of the humans that visit your site but nevertheless, this upgrade does ensure that the data you find within your ORBTR tracking is more focused and valuable than ever before.</p>\n<h3>Our integration with Gravity Forms is better than ever!</h3>\n<p>Our legacy ORBTR integration (the familiar checkbox under form settings) has been replaced with a more powerful feature that allows you to map your form fields to ORBTR. This is a much more powerful feature than the original and also corrects a software conflict some ORBTR users were experiencing with the latest version of Gravity Forms.</p>\n<p><em><strong>NOTE: </strong>Existing ORBTR users will need to redo all their existing form integrations when they upgrade — we realize that this will be a one-time hassle but it is crucial as we are not only improving the functionality but also correcting a bug with the new version of Gravity Forms which may prevent ORBTR from receiving lead information from your site.</em></p>\n<p>Instructions for using the new integration are in the video below:<br />\n<iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/121279779\" width=\"700\" height=\"438\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\n<h3>Better browser and OS recognition</h3>\n<p>ORBTR now recognizes all of the following browsers and operating systems in our lead tracking:</p>\n\n<div class=\"themify_builder_content themify_builder_content-3741 themify_builder not_editable_builder\">\n\n	\n			<!-- module_row -->\n			<div  data-gutter=\"gutter-default\" class=\"themify_builder_row themify_builder_3741_row module_row module_row_0 clearfix gutter-default\" data-equal-column-height=\"\" data-column-alignment=\"\">\n\n		\n				\n				<div class=\"row_inner_wrapper\">\n					<div class=\"row_inner\">\n\n						\n						\n							\n		<div  class=\"col3-1 first tb-column  tb_3741_column module_column\" >\n\n			\n			\n			<div class=\"tb-column-inner\">\n\n				\n				\n					\n<!-- module text -->\n<div id=\"text-3741-0-0-1\" class=\"module module-text text-3741-0-0-1   \">\n	\n	\n	<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Browsers<br /></strong>BlackBerry Browser<br /><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Camino<br /></span><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Kindle / Silk<br /></span><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Firefox / Iceweasel<br /></span><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Safari<br /></span><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Internet Explorer<br /></span><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">IEMobile<br /></span><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Chrome<br /></span><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Opera<br /></span><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Midori<br /></span><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Vivaldi<br /></span><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">TizenBrowser<br /></span><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Lynx<br /></span><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Wget<br /></span><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Curl</span></p>\n	</div>\n<!-- /module text -->\n\n				\n			</div><!-- /.tb-column-inner -->\n					</div>\n		<!-- /.tb-column -->\n		\n		\n		<div  class=\"col3-1 middle tb-column  tb_3741_column module_column\" >\n\n			\n			\n			<div class=\"tb-column-inner\">\n\n				\n				\n					\n<!-- module text -->\n<div id=\"text-3741-0-1-1\" class=\"module module-text text-3741-0-1-1   \">\n	\n	\n	<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Desktop OS</strong><br /> Windows<br /> Linux<br /> Macintosh<br /> Chrome OS</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Mobile OS</strong><br /> Android<br /> iPhone<br /> iPad<br /> Windows Phone OS<br /> Kindle<br /> Kindle Fire<br /> BlackBerry<br /> Playbook<br /> Tizen</p>\n	</div>\n<!-- /module text -->\n\n				\n			</div><!-- /.tb-column-inner -->\n					</div>\n		<!-- /.tb-column -->\n		\n		\n		<div  class=\"col3-1 last tb-column  tb_3741_column module_column\" >\n\n			\n			\n			<div class=\"tb-column-inner\">\n\n				\n				\n					\n<!-- module text -->\n<div id=\"text-3741-0-2-1\" class=\"module module-text text-3741-0-2-1   \">\n	\n	\n	<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Console OS</strong><br /> Nintendo 3DS<br /> New Nintendo 3DS<br /> Nintendo Wii<br /> Nintendo WiiU<br /> PlayStation 3<br /> PlayStation 4<br /> PlayStation Vita<br /> Xbox 360<br /> Xbox One</p>\n	</div>\n<!-- /module text -->\n\n				\n			</div><!-- /.tb-column-inner -->\n					</div>\n		<!-- /.tb-column -->\n		\n		\n								\n								\n							\n						</div>\n						<!-- /row_inner -->\n					</div>\n					<!-- /row_inner_wrapper -->\n				</div>\n				<!-- /module_row -->\n		\n\n</div>\n<h3>Bug fixes</h3>\n<p>Yes, there are always bug fixes&#8230; In addition to the Gravity Forms fix mentioned earlier, the only other notable fix — outside of various API-side performance enhancements — has corrected an issue that was preventing 1), notification emails for leads as they were added to Orbits and, 2), notification emails for returning leads within specific Orbits from being delivered properly.</p>\n<h3>ORBTR 2.9.1 is available now!</h3>\n<p>Current subscribers should see the update available in their WordPress websites right now. Please <a href=\"https://orbtr.net/contact-us/\">contact us</a> with any questions at all!</p>\n<div id=\"themify_builder_content-3739\" data-postid=\"3739\" class=\"themify_builder_content themify_builder_content-3739 themify_builder themify_builder_front\">\n\n	</div>\n<!-- /themify_builder_content --><p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://orbtr.net/blog/orbtr-releases-bot-less-version-2-9-1/\">ORBTR releases &#8220;Bot-Less&#8221; version 2.9.1</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://orbtr.net\">ORBTR.NET - Sales &amp; Marketing Wordpress Plugin</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"https://orbtr.net/blog/orbtr-releases-bot-less-version-2-9-1/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:48:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:47:\"What should you do BEFORE marketing automation?\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:46:\"https://orbtr.net/blog/marketing-automation-2/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"https://orbtr.net/blog/marketing-automation-2/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 20 Jan 2015 16:27:05 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Beginners\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"Marketing Automation Advice\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"https://orbtr.net/?p=3610\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:611:\"<p>Marketing tends to get a bad reputation, not entirely undeserved. Most businesses are doing it wrong. To them, marketing is a line item, a necessary expense. They go through the motions, short on strategy and long on tactics. Yes, tactics can provide a slight advantage over competitors, but most are highly replicable. The mechanics of [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://orbtr.net/blog/marketing-automation-2/\">What should you do BEFORE marketing automation?</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://orbtr.net\">ORBTR.NET - Sales &amp; Marketing Wordpress Plugin</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"admin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14139:\"<p><img src=\'http://orbtr.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/before-automation.jpg\'></p><p>Marketing tends to get a bad reputation, not entirely undeserved. Most businesses are doing it wrong. To them, marketing is a line item, a necessary expense. They go through the motions, short on strategy and long on tactics. Yes, tactics can provide a slight advantage over competitors, but most are highly replicable.</p>\n<p>The mechanics of marketing are actually fairly simple and if you want to properly invest in marketing tools, such as websites and marketing automation software, you need to have a fundamental understanding of how marketing works on a technical level. With the internet, technical wherewithal can beat large marketing budgets.</p>\n<p>If you want to know how to market better than your competitors at a fraction of the price, this article (<a href=\"https://orbtr.net/beginners-guide-to-automation/\">and this ebook</a>) is for you.</p>\n<h3>A few terms you should know</h3>\n<p>We use the following terms frequently in all our writing and you’ll want to know them too as you research topics related to marketing automation:</p>\n<p><strong>Visitors</strong> are anonymous people who visit your website or have shown other interest in your business.</p>\n<p><strong>A lead</strong> is a person who has in some way, shape, or form indicated interest in your company&#8217;s product or service. You have information such as names and email addresses for leads.</p>\n<p><strong>Lead generation</strong> is a process by which you nurture visitors to convert them to leads.</p>\n<p><strong>Lead nurturing</strong> is a process by which you nurture leads over time to convert them to buyers/customers/clients.</p>\n<p><strong>Inbound Marketing</strong> is the process of attracting people to your business &#8211; it helps to have a customer centric view of your business to understand what attracts them, as opposed to forcing your message on them and hoping they convert. People who are interested in your business will visit your website. By collecting their information, you convert visitors into leads. With this information, you can nurture leads until they are motivated to buy your product or service. Ideally, you don’t just get customers, you create advocates for your business.</p>\n<p><strong>Marketing automation</strong> is software that is used to streamline, automate, and measure marketing tasks and workflows, so businesses can increase operational efficiency.</p>\n<!-- shortcode box --> <div class=\"shortcode clearfix box gray note\"><strong>Side note: </strong>Most businesses stop marketing as soon as their leads become customers, but going a little further can yield big results. When you delight customers they will tell friends and continue to buy from you. You should continuously reward everyone for their behavior at every step.</div> <!-- /shortcode box -->\n<p>Marketing automation improves marketing processes such as lead generation, segmentation (separating your leads into groups), lead nurturing and ranking leads, relationship marketing (continuing a dialogue with a lead), cross-sell and up-sell, and customer retention.</p>\n<h3>Deciding where to do your marketing</h3>\n<p>A big business marketing effort is usually the advertising equivalent of a “shock and awe” campaign: carefully integrated efforts across multiple media including television, billboards, magazines, web, social and mobile.</p>\n<p>But small businesses, constrained by limits with time and money, are often put in situations where they have to pick and choose what they want to pursue. We have to eliminate mass media advertising (like television, radio and print) off the bat, because there’s almost no way that small businesses can afford enough repetition to get any return on the investment (ROI). So, that leaves word of mouth and online marketing as primary tools.</p>\n<h3>A small business marketer’s canvas</h3>\n<p>In open air markets, booths of people could market by shouting offers into the crowd and give demonstrations or free samples to a passersby. Simply yelling into the streets isn’t going to work unless you want people to think you are crazy. Most of us don’t sell in open air markets anymore. Instead, we have the internet. On the internet, we have specific channels through which we can shout offers and give demonstrations. These channels are:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Blogging (on our own or other websites)</li>\n<li>Social media (Facebook, Linkedin, Nextdoor&#8230;)</li>\n<li>Email marketing (Constant Contact, Mailchimp, Salesforce&#8230;)</li>\n<li>Search Engine Optimization (SEO on your own site)</li>\n<li>Search Engine Marketing (SEM or Pay Per Click/PPC on search engines like Google)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>With limited time and money, what can we accomplish online? Do we do Search Engine Optimization or social media? Do we start an email newsletter or write an eBook?</p>\n<p>A lot of small businesses feel that they only have time and/or money to pursue one of these initiatives at once. But, you can start at square #1.</p>\n<h3>Your blog is the fuel that runs your marketing engine!</h3>\n<p>Marketing automation software will not help unless you have a healthy supply of relevant visitors. Blogging fuels visitors in a way that no other single investment in time, money or resources can.</p>\n<p>Success in any online marketing initiative hinges upon your content, which is the bait that attracts prospects to your site. Yes, there are still SEO consultants who will perpetuate the myth that SEO is based on the proliferation of secret keywords on your website. There are similarly devious “social media experts” who will try to make you believe that success is all about how many followers you have. Both of these claims are 100% false. The only way to find real, sustainable success in either of these initiatives is through the creation and sharing of original, high quality content, and the same goes for just about everything in the online marketing sphere. Writing and posting at least one 300-600 word blog post per week provides you with at least 1,200-2,400 words of quality content per month and 14,400-28,800 words per year. Those are valuable assets that can easily be leveraged for your benefit. You can put that bait into any number of traps.</p>\n<p>I use the graphic below in presentations to illustrate how blogging directly influences every online marketing initiative a company is likely to have.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-3612\" src=\"https://orbtr.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/tree2-01.jpg\" alt=\"tree2-01\" width=\"960\" height=\"540\" srcset=\"https://orbtr.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/tree2-01.jpg 960w, https://orbtr.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/tree2-01-300x169.jpg 300w, https://orbtr.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/tree2-01-630x354.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\" /></p>\n<p><strong>Email Marketing:</strong> Most business owners will acknowledge the value of an email newsletter to a marketing plan. Some email marketing services encourage you to use these big, elaborate, magazine style newsletter templates that take forever to write and populate.</p>\n<p>A fancy template is completely unnecessary. The more complicated the email, the less likely anyone is to read it. An easy and effective alternative is to use a simple template, lead with a friendly, personalized note about what you and your colleagues are up to, and link to your best two or three blog posts from the month. Now your email is done and, thanks to blogging, it only took you a few minutes.</p>\n<p>Autoresponders (drip email marketing) is also an important piece of the puzzle for many businesses. These messages — sent on a predetermined schedule based on when an individual is added to your list — should serve to help develop your relationship with the individuals on your list and appear almost as personal messages. Almost all of these messages, designed to nurture and build rapport, should feature an excuse for the individual to come back to your site. Blog posts make an excellent means of facilitating this.</p>\n<p><strong>SEO:</strong> By now it should be no secret that Google loves seeing original, relevant content on websites. More than ever before, Google is weighing the frequency of those updates heavily in their algorithm.</p>\n<p>That’s an advantage, not a liability, for bloggers. Blogging ensures that our websites are updated weekly and will grow by 52 pages over the course of a year. As an added bonus, SEO is made a lot simpler thanks to blogging.</p>\n<p><strong>Social Media:</strong> The really successful people in social media aren’t necessarily the ones with the most followers; they’re the ones who contribute most to their followers through developing a unique perspective and sharing high quality content. Business owners struggle with what they should talk about or where they should find conversation topics. Blogging gives you a 300-600 word head start every week. Your social media strategy is a no-brainer thanks to blogging.</p>\n<p><strong>White Papers, eBooks + Presentations:</strong> When you’re creating a couple thousand words of content each and every month, you’re not just creating blog posts, you’re creating building blocks. With some editing, these can easily be used to build other content. The white paper that normally takes three months to write now gets done naturally as part of your weekly blogging effort. The creation of long-form content (like this article) can be low-hanging fruit thanks to blogging.</p>\n<p><strong>Networking:</strong> Whether we’re talking about online or in-person networking, the ability to demonstrate value and the ability to follow-up are crucial. Blog posts make wonderful follow-ups and provide great context for anyone looking to do business with you whether as a client, vendor or referral partner. All your follow-ups just got easier thanks to blogging.</p>\n<p><strong>Landing Pages and Pay Per Click:</strong> You may be wondering how I can possibly tie these efforts into blogging. Easily. Success in AdWords is all about having a relevant offer and the ability to demonstrate value quickly. Blog posts yield eBooks and whitepapers, and eBooks and white papers are great tools to leverage in landing pages and AdWords campaigns. Google rewards these high quality landing pages by lowering your cost per click. Online advertising campaigns can be more affordable and meaningful thanks to blogging.</p>\n<p><strong>Mobile:</strong> Business owners frequently ask me about building mobile apps or starting SMS text message campaigns. Executed well, these initiatives can bring tremendous ROI. Like most online marketing, these initiatives require content. By now, I hope it’s sunk in that blogging is a great way to create that content.</p>\n<p>No, blogging is not a “silver bullet”; you still need to focus on these other initiatives and they will still take time and effort, but they will take significantly less time and effort thanks to blogging. There’s no other single initiative that can have the same impact on your strategy as a whole. If marketing can be made much easier by blogging, why not do it all?</p>\n<h3>Attract people with good content</h3>\n<p>Deciding what to write about is where many blogging initiatives go wrong. Many business owners fall into the trap of trying to make their website the authoritative resource for everything to do with their industry. This is a tempting impulse, but usually wrong. Unless you are serving an incredibly niche market, the cold/hard information about what you’re doing likely already exists online and is going to be a much more complete resource than you could create in a reasonable amount of time.</p>\n<p>Instead, we recommend that you focus on <strong>perspective</strong> in your blog posts, the reason your customers come to you in the first place. They may know a certain type of product or service is important already — they’re on your website after all — but they may not know how to apply it or what they should look for when purchasing. This is the type of information that you should be trying to convey in your posts, the same kind of information that you discuss when you talk to a client over the phone or pitch a prospect in their conference room. Your perspective and experience is most often what gets your firm hired, so keep your writing focus there.</p>\n<h3>Here is a short list of writing tips:</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Try to retain your personality and the personality of your brand and write conversationally as much as possible — think of blogs as your virtual salesperson and present information in writing as you would want to in person. If that personality is analytical, entertaining, witty, wise, etc., try to incorporate that into your posts.</li>\n<li>Frequently asked questions make excellent blog posts and sales follow-ups.</li>\n<li>Tips on how to hire or select a firm in your industry or tips on how to avoid traps clients typically fall into are also very good topics to address.</li>\n<li>Answering objections to hiring or misconceptions about your industry make great posts and are extremely useful in your sales and marketing process.</li>\n<li>Don’t worry about making each post perfect. The nature of blogging is to be a perpetual work in progress where you build on your ideas post by post, where you can always go back and tweak things and where you can flesh out complex thoughts over time.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>For more details about blogging, check out my book <a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Blog-Business-Leveraging-Marketing-Generation/dp/0986023744/\" target=\"_blank\">Blogging for Business</a>.</p>\n<div id=\"themify_builder_content-3610\" data-postid=\"3610\" class=\"themify_builder_content themify_builder_content-3610 themify_builder themify_builder_front\">\n\n	</div>\n<!-- /themify_builder_content --><p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://orbtr.net/blog/marketing-automation-2/\">What should you do BEFORE marketing automation?</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://orbtr.net\">ORBTR.NET - Sales &amp; Marketing Wordpress Plugin</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"https://orbtr.net/blog/marketing-automation-2/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0: