ficer with more than forty years’ experience developing physical security, decision support, crisis management, and critical infrastructure protection systems and programs in hostile environments.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><strong>Jerry Durant</strong>, <em>Director International Operations</em></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">As the Director International Operations, Mr. Durant is a retired Marine Corps Infantry Officer with than 30 plus years in uniform.  Having served in Vietnam, Afghanistan and Iraq he commanded at every level up to an including a Regimental Combat Team.  A graduate of the U.S. Army’s Command &amp; General Staff College, The School for Advanced Military Studies, the Norwegian Defense College and twice attended Defense Language Institute for Dutch and Norwegian.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><strong>Gary House</strong>, <em>Chief Information Officer</em></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">As the Chief Information Officer, Mr. House plans, designs, and manages the BH Defense information technology (IT) infrastructure, staff, and resources. In this capacity, he directs planning and implementation of all information and technology systems, services, projects, and functions that support the operations of the business. He works directly with all departments within the BH Defense corporate headquarters to help identify inefficiencies in business processes in addition to also ensuring business processes can be streamlined by leveraging technology systems. Mr. House graduated from the University of MD University College and holds many industry standard IT and Security certifications.</span></p>','Our Team','','inherit','open','open','','19-revision-v1','','','2015-04-03 11:50:15','2015-04-03 15:50:15','',19,'http://bhdefense.com/19-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1830,1,'2015-04-23 08:46:48','2015-04-23 12:46:48','<h2>BH Defense: A Broader Vision for Mitigating Risk</h2>\r\n<stron