ed Ambulances used by humanitarian and aid providing organizations.\r\n5.	Armored CIT Vehicles for Banks and well known Jewelry houses.\r\n6.	Armored Passenger Transport extensively used by Oil & Gas organizations operating in fragile environments.\r\n7.	Armored Pickup Trucks employed by military services and private companies.\r\nTAS – Transparent Armor Systems is our wholly owned subsidiary company which enables IAG for in-house certified ballistic glass production which is best suitable armored glass for the vehicle, compatible with the design and imparts the OEM look & protection of the vehicles.  \r\n** Other Armoring companies outsource the glass which is incompatible with the design of Armoring in the car, has already passed half or more of its life expectancy so likely to delaminate in advance and also the prime cause of huge deferments in the vehicle delivery to customers.\r\nAVM- Armor Vehicle Manufacturer is our another owned subsidiary company which allows in-house Laser Cutting Technology which gives the exact figure of millimeter to millimeter cutting  on the ballistic steel which later contributes to utmost alignment and conformity with the exact OEM look of the vehicles. \r\nNot only this we internally fabricate high-end custom interior finishing, advance suspension systems, ambulance conversions and low to high Sulphur diesel engine conversions.\r\nWaiting for your valued feedback for further proceedings to initiate our business relations.\r\nPlease acknowledge receipt of my email. Your cooperation is appreciated!\r\nThanks,\r\n\r\nMs. Ammara Khurshied \r\nMiddle East Operations\r\nInternational Armored Group \r\nP.O Box 50060,Khor Khwair Industrial Park,\r\nRAK Free Trade Zone,\r\nRas Al Khaimah,United Arab Emirates \r\nTel: +971 7 205 7676 (Ext No. 240)\r\nFax: +971 7 266 8969\r\nMobile: +971 558789301\r\nWebsite: www.interarmored.com\r\nE mail: a.khurshied@interarmored.com\r\n      \r\n\"When it comes to protection, there is no other.\"\r\nMember