INSERT INTO `wp_rg_lead_detail_long` VALUES (5,'Sir or Ma\'am\r\nI am a Reconnaissance Marine looking to provide protective security for your company. If there are any openings in PSD/PSS or Designated Marksmanship, please let me know where to send a resume. Thank you for your time.'),(10,'How To Increase Your Website Ranking And Traffic \r\n \r\nWe can get your website on top of search Engines. All work will be done as per Google\'s guidelines (Panda, penguin and hummingbird). Please reply on this e-mail for more info. (Guaranteed Results)\r\n'),(14,'Greating \r\nI was working with your company in iraq from 2005 to 2008 and i need your help because my life and my family life are in danger and in great threat.and i my supervisor name (Charles Dublin) and i was member of his bodyguard team.and i hope to get any help from you.and any chance to get contact with (Charles Dublin) please\r\nI\'m waiting your answer.'),(33,'Charlie,\r\nI realized I lost your private contact information so I just wanted to reach out to see how you are doing ,wanted to check in and make sure that Annita is safe and sound since when I last saw her she was still in Baghdad. I am doing well on my end ,back in Law Enforcement in Georgia.  I hope you are in good health and doing well. Take care and keep in touch from time to time\r\n\r\nKind Regards,\r\nDon Schultz formally OPS Manager PSI.'),(64,'Dear Sir/Madam,\r\n\r\nDuring my career, I have performed a variety of duties in security area in the U.S. Embassy as well as in other organizations. My ten-year experience as a Guard and military experience where I handled different responsibilities including organizing, managing and work planning for subordinate staff, monitoring security posts, conducting professional trainings for subordinate staff, keeping working journals and post documentation, preparing reports, etc., vouchers for my professionalism. \r\n\r\nBest Regards\r\n\r\nDmytro Radchenko'),(80,'I am interested in finding pmc work or other security type opportunities. After I separated from the military (honorable) I attended community college for two years and am now looking to return to a work field that will allow me to utilize the skills I have acquired as a infantryman.'),(95,'While serving as a Military Police Team Leader in the United States Marine Corps, I provided security and force protection in both Iraq and Afghanistan. Throughout my years serving in the Middle East I filled a number of different roles including turret machine gunner and driver for a gun truck while performing route clearance patrols and providing security for logistical convoys, as well as a team leader during security searches of living quarters and company compounds inhabited by third country nationals within U.S. forward operating bases and as a corporal of the guard, responsible for multiple static guard posts and roving patrols.\r\n\r\nMy professional accomplishments include:\r\n\r\n•	Conducted nearly 100 mounted route clearance patrols in Al Anbar Provence, Iraq.\r\n•	Conducted well over 100 security details for resupply convoys in Al Anbar Provence, Iraq.\r\n•	Numerous awards for excellence in educational and operational environments.\r\n•	Served as a team leader during nearly 200 internal security patrols and searches of third country nationals’ living quarters and compounds inside of Al Asad Air Base in Al Anbar Provence, Iraq.\r\n•	Logged over 2000 hours as a Corporal of the Guard, supervising multiple guard posts and roving patrols, which secured the flight line and served in a Quick Reaction Force (QRF) in forward operating base Camp Dwyer in Helmand Provence, Afghanistan.\r\n\r\nWith my operational security experience and strong focus on continued education and professional development in mind, I would appreciate the opportunity to further discuss how my qualifications will be beneficial to BH Defense. Thank you for your consideration, I look forward to meeting with you.'),(111,'Stanton Eiland\r\nTamuning Guam 96913\r\nstantoneiland@gmail.com\r\n671 988 9282\r\n\r\nFinishing NAVFAC project in Guan \r\nImmediately available for interview \r\n\r\nI am a highly talented and accomplished Project Management professional of ready mix concrete, precast, airfield paving and quarry industry experience in the United States, Bermuda, UAE, Qatar, Angola, Afghanistan, Mongolia and Liberia with the proven ability for getting jobs done on time, within budget and according to specifications.\r\nMy background is in concrete project management of military airfield paving, nuclear, industrial, and commercial concrete production, supervision, and operations management as well as plant and maintenance facility construction. I have planned and directed numerous projects and I am adept at managing multiple projects. I am skilled in vendor negotiation, compliance reporting, scope development, and client management. I and am able to coordinate and liaison with design and construction professionals, local and federal officials and executive management.\r\nIn addition to my knowledge and experience in concrete and aggregate production, paving management and operations management I also possess well-developed business skills, and am able to serve as primary contact to clients throughout all project phases. I have the ability to determine needs, proposals, and negotiate with clients, vendors, and contractors.\r\nMy experience includes direction of a wide variety of concrete plant and ancillary facility construction, renovation, and development projects. I readily conceptualize new ideas as needed. I am able to plan and coordinate all project phases, from conceptualization and requirement determination through planning, design, and final construction, as well as schedules, direct purchasing and ensure compliance with all safety and building regulations.\r\nI have a well-deserved reputation in this industry for getting jobs done on time and within budget, while maintaining safe, reliable work sites. I am dedicated to providing the highest quality service at all times, and remain actively involved in overseeing and inspecting a site until the project is completed to the client\'s satisfaction.\r\nThank you for your time and consideration.\r\nSincerely, \r\nStanton Eiland\r\n\r\n\r\n'),(147,'Dear Sir or Madam, I am working for the Corporate Security Department of BASF (http://www.basf.com/group/corporate/en/index). I am interested in your whitepapers, corporate brochure and your terms and conditions. Would you please provide me with these documents as PDF? For a confirmation of my status as a business employee in the security branch you can approach the central BASF callcenter (+49 621 60-0) and let you forward to Alexander Hoelzer from GUS/WS (Regional Security Europe/Africa). My phone number above is wrong to meet the US-format for your sheet - my direct number is +49 621 60-43415. Thank you in advance! Regards, Alexander Hoelzer'),(162,'Madame, Monsieur,\r\nEn consultent votre site internet je me permets de vous propose mes services.\r\n\r\n    Fort d’une expérience solide de 16 ans en tant que militaire (Légion Etrangère, 2 REP) et officier de police auparavant, un métier très fort psychologiquement et un travail qui m’a habitué aux ordres, aux consignes et aux procédures les plus strictes. En même temps m’a permis d’avoir nombreuses stages et formations niveaux nationale et internationale, une riche connaissance en armes d’origine différentes, optiques, mines et matière explosives, et de garder mon sang-froid dans les conditions difficiles. Je suis rigoureux dans mon travail et je désire aujourd’hui intégrer une organisation de notoriété afin de continuer à progresser et élargir mes connaissances.\r\n\r\n   Motivée, autonome, dynamique, casier judiciaire vierge, organisé et en excellente conditions physique, je suis disponible pour activités professionnelles. Je vous propose de nous rencontrer afin que vous puissiez juger du sérieux de ma candidature. \r\n\r\n   Je me tiens dans cette attente à votre entière disposition et vous prie d’agréer, Madame, Monsieur, l’expression de ma respectueuse considération. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n                                                                                                             Ivanov Plamen          \r\n'),(194,'Stanton Eiland\r\nTamuning Guam 96913\r\nstantoneiland@gmail.com\r\n671 988 9282\r\n\r\nFinishing NAVFAC project in Guan \r\nImmediately available for interview \r\n\r\nI am a highly talented and accomplished Project Management professional of ready mix concrete, precast, airfield paving and quarry industry experience in the United States, Bermuda, UAE, Qatar, Angola, Afghanistan, Mongolia and Liberia with the proven ability for getting jobs done on time, within budget and according to specifications.\r\nMy background is in concrete project management of military airfield paving, nuclear, industrial, and commercial concrete production, supervision, and operations management as well as plant and maintenance facility construction. I have planned and directed numerous projects and I am adept at managing multiple projects. I am skilled in vendor negotiation, compliance reporting, scope development, and client management. I and am able to coordinate and liaison with design and construction professionals, local and federal officials and executive management.\r\nIn addition to my knowledge and experience in concrete and aggregate production, paving management and operations management I also possess well-developed business skills, and am able to serve as primary contact to clients throughout all project phases. I have the ability to determine needs, proposals, and negotiate with clients, vendors, and contractors.\r\nMy experience includes direction of a wide variety of concrete plant and ancillary facility construction, renovation, and development projects. I readily conceptualize new ideas as needed. I am able to plan and coordinate all project phases, from conceptualization and requirement determination through planning, design, and final construction, as well as schedules, direct purchasing and ensure compliance with all safety and building regulations.\r\nI have a well-deserved reputation in this industry for getting jobs done on time and within budget, while maintaining safe, reliable work sites. I am dedicated to providing the highest quality service at all times, and remain actively involved in overseeing and inspecting a site until the project is completed to the client\'s satisfaction.\r\nThank you for your time and consideration.\r\nSincerely, \r\nStanton Eiland\r\n\r\n\r\n'),(209,'To Whom It May Concern - \r\n\r\nPlease see the attached resume for the above-referenced position. I am confident that my project management, strategic consulting, operational and business management experience will be of significant value to you.  I hold an active TS/SCI with full scope polygraph and have significant customer contacts within Department of Defense, Department of Justice, Homeland Security and Intelligence agencies. \r\n\r\nAfter you review my credentials, please contact me to schedule a time when we can have a discussion. Thank you. \r\n\r\nKevin Manuel-Scott \r\n571-207-5025'),(224,'Versatile professional with project management, business development, and research background primarily in the areas of security, intelligence, emergency management, and capture and proposal activities. Proven ability to support multiple projects simultaneously in a deadline driven environment.  Specialized research in Unconventional Warfare and Terrorism Studies. Possesses DOE Secret L Security Clearance.'),(230,'How To Increase Your Website Ranking And Traffic \r\n \r\nHope you are well.\r\n\r\nI was surfing through your website. When we search for any keyword pertaining to your domain, your website does not come on the first page of Google. So how would people come to know about your website? If you want your website to appear on first page of Google then please let me know. We can provide you certain Top 10 Google rankings.\r\n\r\nI look forward to your Mail.\r\n'),(231,'Hi,\r\n\r\nMy name is Richard. I am wondering if you need a new video for your website or for YouTube?\r\n\r\nIf you are located in Arlington, you can get a pretty good deal on producing a marketing video right now.\r\nhttp://marketingvideostv.com/Examples\r\n\r\nProfessionally produced videos have been proven to boost website traffic, leads and conversions.\r\nYou can get access to some of my best video examples here:\r\n>>http://marketingvideostv.com/Examples\r\n\r\nThanks,\r\nRichard\r\n\r\nPS. If you are going to produce a video, I highly recommend using animation, or even a combination of photos, footage and animation. Animation is less expensive than shooting new footage with a camera and it can be used to make your story interesting and hold the attention of your prospects.\r\n>>http://marketingvideostv.com/Examples'),(232,'Hi,\r\n\r\nMy name is Richard. I am wondering if you need a new video for your website or for YouTube?\r\n\r\nIf you are located in Arlington, you can get a pretty good deal on producing a marketing video right now.\r\nhttp://marketingvideostv.com/Examples\r\n\r\nProfessionally produced videos have been proven to boost website traffic, leads and conversions.\r\nYou can get access to some of my best video examples here:\r\n>>http://marketingvideostv.com/Examples\r\n\r\nThanks,\r\nRichard\r\n\r\nPS. If you are going to produce a video, I highly recommend using animation, or even a combination of photos, footage and animation. Animation is less expensive than shooting new footage with a camera and it can be used to make your story interesting and hold the attention of your prospects.\r\n>>http://marketingvideostv.com/Examples'),(246,'BH Defense, LLC\r\n901 North Stuart Street, Suite 902\r\nArlington, VA 22203\r\n12 December 2014\r\n\r\nDear Sir or Madame,\r\n\r\nGood day!  Though I note that it appears you currently do not have any in-house associate or compliance positions open, I kindly ask you to take a glance at my resume.  \r\n\r\nHaving deployed three times since 2007 in support of the War on Terror, and still serving this great Nation, I am very interested in the possibility of a career with your fascinating company.  I believe the combination of my legal training and the application of my legal skills for various employers supporting the defense industry could make me a good fit for BH Defense.  \r\n\r\nI have served in the military worldwide over twenty years.  I can assist BH Defense with its global compliance requirements, legal contracting review, legal risk analysis, and all other areas of legal endeavor.  I have developed the skill set to effectively advise, negotiate and interact with your customers and your corporate staff, worldwide.\r\n\r\nI currently hold a SECRET security clearance.    \r\n\r\nI have worked multiple times under conditions of duress, long hours and hardship.  I am tenacious in my approach to everything I do, sagacious in identifying the available resources to accomplish those things and humble to defer to those who have greater expertise.  Further, my integrity is unblemished and I bring this to the table when advising those I support.  \r\n\r\nIf you determine I have the attributes BH Defense can use, please contact me so we can further discuss.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nVery Respectfully,\r\nFredrick D. Lambing\r\n'),(289,'Dear Hiring Manager, \r\nI am writing to express my interest in working for BH Defense and to expound upon how my background and strengths might suit any openings you have for a research analyst. As a recent graduate of an M.Phil. in International Relations and Politics program at the University of Cambridge, I would relish the opportunity to apply my research and writing experience to the diversity of projects on which your firm works. I am particularly attracted to BH Defense’s reputation as an up-and-coming industry leader with wide-ranging expertise and resources. \r\nMy academic coursework and independent study have encompassed diverse regional and security topics. I graduated summa cum laude from the University of Southern California in May 2013 with a firm grasp of international security studies, Mandarin Chinese, and Chinese political history. Wishing to gain a greater academic understanding of other issue-areas that I had mostly tracked through independent readings, I completed coursework in Middle Eastern and North African (MENA) politics, East African security, and international constitutional law for my master’s degree. \r\nIn addition to my coursework this past year, I undertook two prominent research projects detailed in my résumé: “The ICC’s Prosecution of Sitting Heads of State” and “Unlawful Killings in Africa.” The former, which I submitted as my master’s dissertation, explores Presidents Omar al-Bashir\'s and Uhuru Kenyatta\'s political maneuverings to contest and counterbalance the ICC, analyzing how the Court\'s investigations shape Sudanese and Kenyan governance and affect, directly or indirectly, the victims and witnesses of mass atrocity crimes in the Darfur War in Sudan and in the 2007-08 post-election violence in Kenya. My chapter contribution to “Unlawful Killings in Africa,” a 268-page report written in collaboration with the UN special rapporteur on extrajudicial, summary or arbitrary executions, details extrajudicial killings by civilian mass actors in more than 30 African states, requiring extensive background research into sub-Saharan political and security issues.       \r\nBeyond my academic background, my extracurricular pursuits at USC refined skills integral to work at BH Defense. As the Sports Editor of USC’s daily newspaper, I wrote articles on tight deadlines and edited hundreds of submitted stories for structure, syntax, and grammar before fact-checking them for accuracy. These late nights in the office molded me into a more efficient, precise, and technically sound writer, preparing me to produce the high volume and different forms of writing expected of a researcher. These positions also developed my leadership, administrative, and interpersonal skills. Running an award-winning student newspaper section dictated that I learn how to motivate and position my predominantly unpaid writers to produce their best work. As an Orientation Adviser, I conducted campus tours and spoke on student panels, polishing my public speaking skills in small, informal settings and in larger forums — transferable experience for any oral presentations I would make.\r\nIf hired, I would promise to bring my tireless work ethic to BH Defense. Thank you for your consideration, and I look forward to the opportunity to speak with you in person about my interest in this position. \r\nSincerely,\r\nSean McCormick'),(350,'Good day to you! My friend works for you, in Baghdad, a doctor Yuri Stolyarov. If you need medical workers, on one of your sites, please contact me by e-mail: khlyostkin@yahoo.com\r\nThank you in advance!'),(366,'From:  \r\n\r\nMohammad. Emran\r\nEHS Advisor/Officer\r\nLarsen & Toubro Oman llc (L&T)\r\nRuwi, Oman\r\n\r\n  Sub:  Application for HSE Officer/Engineer\r\n\r\nTo\r\nThe General Manger /HRM\r\n\r\nRespected Sir, \r\n\r\nIf your organization is seeking a skilled and experienced HSE Advisor or Officer, I wish to apply for the same. My enclosed resume provides you with an overview of my relevant Education, experience and training. I’d delighted to discuss my application further with you. I can be easily contacted by phone +968 98700599 (Oman), 0091 9199848942 or email.\r\n\r\nI look forward to hearing from you.\r\n\r\nThank you for your consideration.\r\n\r\nThanks & Regards\r\n\r\nMohammad. Emran\r\n\r\nCell #    +968 -98700599 (Oman)\r\n             +91-9199848942 (India)      \r\n'),(399,'I was hoping to connect to your company’s IT Manager or someone who handles your ICT needs as I was hoping to introduce our company and its services.\r\n\r\nVizocom is a Global Satellite Service Provider, but in UAE where we operate from, we offer the full ICT services including but not limited to IT Infrastructures, CCTV Installations, PAGA and Audio Visual Solutions, and Procurement.\r\n\r\nThank you in advance and hope to hear from you soon.\r\n'),(413,'COVER LETTER\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n									\r\nStara strugara C/36\r\n36350 Raska, Serbia\r\nCell:+381-618049019\r\ne/mail: dzadzon@gmail.com\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nDear,\r\n\r\nI\'m 41 years old. I believe that my many years of experience  can help a lot of your program. I worked at jobs in the security sector and I have a rich experience.  I have experience as a civilian and military EMT, Paramedic and Armor guard. I\'m an ex military EMT in the Special Parachute Brigade and 37. Infantry brigade of the Army of Serbia. I am a member of the voluntary rescue team of the Municipality of Raska. I am a participant in two wars. In the last war I was extraordinarily promoted because of my merits in defense of the country.  \r\nI hope that you will be interested in my CV. All other documents will send you on your request.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nSincerely \r\nUros Despotovic\r\n\r\n\r\n'),(443,'Good Day\r\nMy name is Willem Thysse and I am from South-Africa.\r\nI would like to inquire if you have any security positions available.\r\nI am an experienced security contractor with international experience in the commercial and government sectors. My most recent appointment was an Explosive Detection Dog-handler and I also served as manager / kennel master at some of the FOBS in Afghanistan.  I also have Narcotic-Detection-handler experience as well as PSD training and I was in the South-African Police Service for 17 years.\r\nI believe I will be an asset to your company. I am hard-working and trustworthy and would like to be part of your team. I am fit to travel and am immediately available to deploy if needed. I have a valid passport and also an USA visa.\r\nMy CV attached for your attention.\r\nThank you for the opportunity\r\n'),(458,'Raymond J. Vargas JR\r\n377 Delta Drive West\r\nHattiesburg, MS 39402\r\n(601) 818-3036\r\nvargas547_1999@yahoo.com \r\n\r\nTo BH Defense,\r\n\r\nAs my resume indicates, I am a retired U.S Army senior enlisted with over 21 years of leadership, management, training, security, and operations experience. I have over ten years in management and coordination of support services management. I have over four years’ experience contracting in the defense industry. I have experience interacting with a multitude of government agencies to include: Department of State (DOS), Department of Defense (DOD).  I have experienced advising, training and interacting with foreign militaries and governments. I have over 20 years’ experience directing, integrating and coordinating a multitude of management systems and functional support areas to include: project controls, accounting, finance, procurement, subcontracts, property control, document control, HR, and IT/communications. I am well versed in all human resource functions to include: payroll, travel, benefits, recruit administrative actions, interviewing, and foreign country naturalization processes. I have a strong working knowledge of all Microsoft applications to include: Microsoft word, Excel, Access and PowerPoint. I also have working knowledge of Visio. I am also knowledgeable in all logistics and support areas. I have experience managing foreign company’s sub-contracts. I have a strong working knowledge of regulations such as the FAR, ITAR, EAR, and DFAR.\r\n\r\nWhile serving in the army, have held many senior enlisted management positions.  I also have over 20 years’ experience as a manager and military trainer. I have managed both operations and support services in Germany, Macedonia, and Saudi Arabia. As a trainer for 1st Army, I have experience in both Afghanistan and Iraq, deploying with units for their first month in country. I have served as a senior enlisted advisor to a Saudi Arabian National Guard Brigade in the past. I have also trained Kuwait National Guard Soldiers and Iraq Army Soldiers. I have coordinated joint training exercises with German, Russian and Bulgarian Soldiers. \r\n\r\nI have a Master’s of Science in Management (Human Resource Management concentration) degree through Bellevue University. I have a Bachelor’s of Science in Management (Human Resource Management concentration) through the same university. In the near term I hope to take both the PMP and SPHR exams. I have completed many leadership courses while in the army.\r\n\r\nI believe I would be a great fit for your organization for a position in Human Resource Management, Operations Management, Service Support Management, Security, Program Management, Military Trainer, Trainer Advisor, Logistics Management, and Project Management. My vast knowledge across different agencies and countries would be a valuable asset to your organization. I am very motivated and very resourceful. I take the initiative to find answers to problems. I pick up procedures, processes and systems really quick. I enjoy working with people of all races and cultures. Most of all with me you get a strong team member and team builder, someone who is constantly seeking self-improvement. I have experience living, working and driving in Middle East countries and understand the customs and courtesies of the Middle East. I am seeking a position overseas: South Sudan, Iraq, Afghanistan; I will consider any other positions in the Middle East, Africa, Europe, and Asia.\r\n\r\nFinally, I hope that this may lead to an interview so we can discuss a potential future I may have with your organization. If you have any question or to set up any interview, please call me at (601) 818-3036 or email me at vargas547_1999@yahoo.com . Thank you.\r\n\r\nBest regards,\r\nRaymond J. Vargas JR\r\n\r\n\r\n'),(474,'My name is Richard and I am Wordpress  security expert. While browsing your site bhdefense.com, I found that your site is vulnerable to hackers. I have prepared detailed security audit report for bhdefense.com. Please visit www.perfectwordpresssecurity.com/report/bhdefense.com  to view the security vulnerabilities to your website. I have also added screenshot of your website to show you that which pages can be accessed by hackers. Everyday 30000+ Wordpress sites are hacked! Your wordpress website should not be victim of one of those malicious attacks. If you have any questions, please feel free to email me for FREE consultancy at sales@perfectwordpresssecurity.com'),(475,'My name is Richard and I am Wordpress  security expert. While browsing your site bhdefense.com, I found that your site is vulnerable to hackers. I have prepared detailed security audit report for bhdefense.com. Please visit www.perfectwordpresssecurity.com/report/bhdefense.com  to view the security vulnerabilities to your website. I have also added screenshot of your website to show you that which pages can be accessed by hackers. Everyday 30000+ Wordpress sites are hacked! Your wordpress website should not be victim of one of those malicious attacks. If you have any questions, please feel free to email me for FREE consultancy at sales@perfectwordpresssecurity.com'),(476,'Hi!\r\n\r\nSorry to bother you...\r\n\r\nI am trying to connect with the person responsible for video marketing so I can send them a free copy of this cheat sheet for creating their own video \'conversion formula\'.\r\n\r\nPerhaps you can pass this on?\r\n\r\nThey can get their free cheat sheet here: http://MarketingVideosTV.com/437Conversion-Formula/\r\n\r\nThanks,\r\nMichelle Shenny\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nIf you would rather be removed from my contact list you can do that too:\r\nhttp://MarketingVideosTV.com/remove/\r\nThank you!'),(477,'Hi!\r\n\r\nSorry to bother you...\r\n\r\nI am trying to connect with the person responsible for video marketing so I can send them a free copy of this cheat sheet for creating their own video \'conversion formula\'.\r\n\r\nPerhaps you can pass this on?\r\n\r\nThey can get their free cheat sheet here: http://MarketingVideosTV.com/437Conversion-Formula/\r\n\r\nThanks,\r\nMichelle Shenny\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nIf you would rather be removed from my contact list you can do that too:\r\nhttp://MarketingVideosTV.com/remove/\r\nThank you!'),(506,'02 March 2014\r\nGreetings Human Resource Management Professional; \r\nI am contacting you concerning an employment opportunity with BH Defense.  I have attached a current copy of my resume, for your review. I am more than willing to relocate outside of the United States.   I have more than 20 years of combined military and civilian experience in the field of logistics; I have an active, Department of Defense issued, Secret security clearance, and I have extensive education and training in the civilian and military logistical field. I am also a certified Property Book Unit Supply Enhanced (PBUSE / (Property Book User)).  I would greatly appreciate any assistance that you could possibly extend to me. Please feel free to contact me with any additional comments, questions or concerns. I look forward to your reply.\r\n\r\nVery respectfully,\r\n\r\nRobert T. Dozier\r\n\r\nTop Ten Reasons to Hire a Veteran\r\n\r\n1. Accelerated Learning Curve\r\n2. Leadership\r\n3. Teamwork\r\n4. Diversity and Inclusion in Action\r\n5. Efficient performance under pressure\r\n6. Respect for procedures\r\n7. Technology and globalization\r\n8. Integrity\r\n9. Conscious of health and safety standards \r\n10. Triumph over adversity\r\n'),(521,'Dear Sir or Madame\r\nI am a retired Croatian Army NCO. I was honorable discharged after working 16 years in Croatian Armed Forces, Military Intelligence unit and Police Forces at various levels of command. My main responsibility was to plan, manage, facilitate and conduct information collection in order to support Safety, Security and Force Protection efforts. As a te