oples. Through my traveling, I have gained an understanding of professionalism as a foreigner under the customs of other cultures and laws. I am willing to relocate anywhere in the world with short notice.'),(4242,'Dear employers\r\nI am applying for the position of security officer as detailed on your website. I have held positions that are similar to the one that you described, and I feel that my previous employment has prepared me specifically for a position like this. Specifically, \r\nMy 14 years of security experience provided me with ample opportunities to hone and perfect my skills On numerous occasions, during my tenure as a security officer, in Ministry of Defence-ARMY I have received accolades from management for my successful handling of emergency situations and work positions-Security in Afghanistan-HQ ISAF -Protection of Force, armored car DRIVER and Escord, QRF, SCANNER operator-PLATFORM FOR PEOPLE AND VEHICLES, Armed security tower guard, MARITIME SECURITY OFFICER-armed\r\nThis message is to express my interest in working in your company, and putting my extensive military experience.Establish and maintain a stable position in your company, where through hard work and competence\r\nLoyal and responsible, good for finding solutions I am an honest, hard working, punctual, and grounded person. These qualities have kept me in good stead in my professional life and I believe will serve me well in the future too.\r\nYou can further read details about my professional achievements, job responsibilities, work experience, and academic qualifications in my resume, which is attached with this application for your perusal. I would welcome an opportunity to meet you in person or interview to discuss for my suitability for the job.\r\nThank you for considering my application no matter what you decide to do. I hope to see you at the next stage of the hiring process, and I look forward to your correspondence.. I sent my resume for your consideration for a position in your company.\r\nThank you….with respect NIKOLA'),(4263,'Hello, I am a citizen of Georgia, I served in the Special Forces for 13 years, I was in Iraq and Afghanistan, and I took part in the war between Russia and Georgia in 2008, I was in a combat zone (ATO) in Ukraine, I would like to know, I have I have a chance to find a job in your company?'),(4293,'Seeks an opportunity to utilize my extensive 15+ Years of US Military and UN Mission Armory Logistic & Weapon Maintenance experience for the position of Logistic – Maintenance – Coordinator - Manager / Small Arms – Crew Served Weapons Repairman – Armory Specialist – Armorer /ANA & ANP’s US Military & NATO Weapon Instructor /Personnel Transport – Maritime Security – Armed Guard\r\nSkills & Experience IN :  “US Military Base Security Armorer - Armed Guard – NCC- OSHA- Maritime STCW2010 - STSDSD  Armory Property Logistic - Weapons M4 – M9 – M249- M240- M2-  AK47 High Risk Environment,  Kuwait – Sudan – Afghanistan - Iraq  ” \r\nØ	2015 Nov – Jan 2016 worked  as a  Armorer , REED Inc , SOSI Camp Besmaya, Bagdad, Iraq\r\n  Armorer - Armory Custodian – Logistic Property Assistant'),(4309,'For over twenty-five years I have been responsible for safety, security and community relations in numerous hostile, high risk and remote environments and communities worldwide. I have worked with several oil, gas and mining exploration companies as well as various media companies in some of their most difficult, demanding and challenging operations. \r\nMy experience in the oil industry includes both maritime and land based oil exploration, geographic, geological and seismic surveying, drilling, production, pipelines and refineries. In Sudan I was responsible for the safety of seismic experts in a remote swamp area in the south of the country. In Ethiopia, I was security focal point for a team of aerial seismic experts throughout the hostile Ogaden region. In Colombia I was responsible for the security of three oil rigs in the volatile Casanare region and in Yemen I was responsible for the security of the construction of an oil export pipeline across the disputed tribal areas of Shabwah and Marib. In Nigeria I advised the crisis management team and negotiated with local tribal chiefs after an offshore oil rig was overrun and staff held hostage, and in Libya I was the Operations Liaison Coordinator for Repsol, securing the re-start operations post civil war and managing the rising civil and community unrest. \r\nIn general, my work has involved overseeing the physical safety of staff, developing bespoke training programs for national and expatriate personnel, training and managing guards, implementing standard operating procedures, and maintaining an appropriate security profile for the risk environment. I focus on keeping company staff secure and preventing conflict with the local communities by instigating a two-way flow of information to keep lines of dialogue open. I believe that core to the company’s continued safety and that of its operations is the involvement with and commitment to the local communities living in the areas in which it is operating.\r\nAs a former Royal Marines Commando with eleven years service, I bring significant military training and experience, which I have adapted to suit the civilian environment. I look forward to the opportunity of becoming on of your consultants and to adding to your reputation and experience.\r\nKind regards\r\n \r\nMartin Vowles'),(4315,'We can put your website on 1st page of Google to drive relevant traffic to your site. Let us know if you would be interested in getting detailed proposal. We can also schedule a call & will be pleased to explain our services in detail. We look forward to hearing from you soon. Thanks!'),(4374,'Dear,\r\n\r\nConsultant specializing in private security sector, and particularly in close protection and risk management in hostile environment, I am currently available and offers my services for the realization of punctual or extended missions.\r\nMy skills, qualifications and experiences enable me to act on all specters of private security, ranging from prevention, risk anticipation, emergency protection plan implementation, crisis management, to defensive actions.\r\nBeing also very sensitive to the commercial, human and confidential requirements of this activity, I can give special care to your customers to give them satisfaction in the performance of the mission, but also to retain loyalty to the services offered by your company.\r\n\r\nYou will find enclosed a copy of my resume.\r\n\r\nI am, of course, at your disposal for any questions, inquiries or interviews that you deem necessary.\r\n\r\nYours sincerly,\r\n\r\nBenjamin BOUILLIÉ');
